Computer graphics involves creating, manipulating, and displaying visual content using computers. It includes digital images, animations, and interactive graphics used in various fields like entertainment and education. Computer graphics can be used for UI design, rendering, geometric objects, and animation. It requires different technologies for creation and manipulation.

Hardware components in computer graphics include the CPU, GPU, memory, and display devices like CRT, LCD, and LED. Input devices like keyboards, mice, graphic tablets, and output devices like monitors, printers, and plotters allow users to interact with computer graphics systems.

Different types of computer graphics include raster graphics, vector graphics, 3D graphics, interactive graphics, and real-time graphics. Animation in computer graphics involves creating a sequence of frames using interpolation techniques. Raster and vector graphics are common types of digital images, each with its own characteristics and uses.

Rendering in computer graphics involves visualizing data, with techniques like scanline, Z-buffer, shading, and lighting used to create realistic images. Output devices like monitors and printers render processed data into visual or physical forms. Overall, computer graphics play a crucial role in various industries and applications.